Etins Records frontline act Christopher Chiké Ajah better known as MORIEN is hoping to end the year on a big note with his new single, Hope, the fast-rising music star said he was looking forward to positive comments and reactions from fans about the song. ALSO READ: ICT: Ogun to host maiden edition of Teachers Fest Morein in an interactive session with Tribune Online on Monday said his next single is not just a song but a prophetic message that is speaking the mind of the 80million Nigerian youths and that of every single soul across the world. According to him, the recent peaceful EndSARS protest by the Nigerian youths portrayed a leadership symbol, one that has clearly shown that ” We deserve a better Nigeria.” “Generally, life has not been fair on many and this song is to ease every single soul out there who has been in one way or the other tired of trying. This is me saying to them that there’s always light at the end of the tunnel let’s keep our ‘HOPE’ alive”. Morienis known for several hits and inspirational songs and this has positioned him in the right place among his contemporaries especially after he released his debut ep “MORIEN EP” in  2019. Unveiling his new single titled “HOPE” with simple yet irresistible soulful and RnB Rhythms, the singer promised music lovers a great sound, adding that he has never gone wrong with his sounds. NIGERIAN TRIBUNE SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that
